Workers rush to finish on Tuesday the last section of the Haoji heavy-haul railway designed to transport coal from North China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region to East China's Jiangxi Province. The 1,837-kilometer railway will be China's longest heavy-haul railway and is set to begin operation in October. Photo: VCG
